9e63933e019'),(2750,278,'info_block_text2','Involves the use of waste oil, either as raw material at the initial stage of the process, or as a coke oven for the production of gasoline and coke.'),(2751,278,'_info_block_text2','field_5a9e63bd3e01d'),(2752,278,'info_block_title3','Regeneration'),(2753,278,'_info_block_title3','field_5a9e63793e016'),(2754,278,'info_block_img3','276'),(2755,278,'_info_block_img3','field_5a9e63993e01a'),(2756,278,'info_block_text3','Involves the treatment of waste oil, removal of contaminants for use as a basis for new lubricating oil. Regeneration extends the life of the oil resource to infinity. This form of processing is preferable, as it completes the recycling cycle by reusing oil to production the same product that the waste oil was originally from, and thus saves energy and natural oil.'),(2757,278,'_info_block_text3','field_5a9e63c33e01e'),(2758,278,'info_block_title4','Processing and burning for energy production:'),(2759,278,'_info_block_title4','field_5a9e63823e017'),(2760,278,'info_block_img4','277'),(2761,278,'_info_block_img4','field_5a9e63a03e01b'),(2762,278,'info_block_text4','Involves the removal of water and particles in such a way that waste oil can be burned, as fuel for heat production or power supply of production operations. This form of processing is not as preferable as the methods for reusing the material, since it allows the used oil to be used only once. Nevertheless, as a result, valuable energy is produced (the same as when using standard fuel oil).'),(2763,278,'_info_block_text4','field_5a9e63c93e01f'),(2764,39,'info_block_title1','<p>On-site restoration</p>'),(2765,39,'_info_block_title1','field_5a9e633c3e014'),(2766,39,'info_block_img1','274'),(2767,39,'_info_block_img1','field_5a9e63883e018'),(2768,39,'info_block_text1','<p>Involves the removal of contaminants from the waste oil and its reuse. Although this form of utilization does not restore oil to its original state, it prolongs its expire date</p>'),(2769,39,'_info_block_text1','field_5a9e63a83e01c'),(2770,39,'info_block_title2','<p>Sending to an oil refinery</p>'),(2771,39,'_info_block_title2','field_5a9e63743e015'),(2772,39,'info_block_img2','275'),(2773,39,'_info_block_img2','field_5a9e63933e019'),(2774,39,'info_block_text2','<p>Involves the use of waste oil, either as raw material at the initial stage of the process, or as a coke oven for the production of gasoline and coke.</p>'),(2775,39,'_info_block_text2','field_5a9e63bd3e01d'),(2776,39,'info_block_title3','<p>Regeneration</p>'),(2777,39,'_info_block_title3','field_5a9e63793e016'),(2778,39,'info_block_img3','276'),(2779,39,'_info_block_img3','field_5a9e63993e01a'),(2780,39,'info_block_text3','<p>Involves the treatment of waste oil, removal of contaminants for use as a basis for new lubricating oil. Regeneration extends the life of the oil resource to infinity. This form of processing is preferable, as it completes the recycling cycle by reusing oil to production the same product that the waste oil was originally from, and thus saves energy and natural oil.</p>'),(2781,39,'_info_block_text3','field_5a9e63c33e01e'),(2782,39,'info_block_title4','<p>Processing and burning for energy production:</p>'),(2783,39,'_info_block_title4','field_5a9e63823e017'),(2784,39,'info_block_img4','277'),(2785,39,'_info_block_img4','field_5a9e63a03e01b'),(2786,39,'info_block_text4','<p>Involves the removal of water and particles in such a way that waste oil can be burned, as fuel for heat production or power supply of production operations. This form of processing is not as preferable as the methods for reusing the material, since it allows the used oil to be used only once. Nevertheless, as a result, valuable energy is produced (the same as when using standard fuel oil).</p>'),(2787,39,'_info_block_text4','field_5a9e63c93e01f'),(2788,74,'field_5aa26bf29258d','a:11:{s:3:\"key\";s:19:\"field_5aa26bf29258d\";s:5:\"label\";s:12:\"text_block_1\";s:4:\"name\";s:12:\"text_block_1\"